                        <outline text="MobSF (Mobile Security Framework) is an open-source mobile application security testing framework that is designed to help security researchers and developers to identify security vulnerabilities in mobile applications."/>
                        <outline text="MobSF is capable of performing various static and dynamic analysis techniques on Android and iOS applications to identify potential security risks such as information leakage, insecure storage, weak cryptography, insecure communication, etc. The tool supports the analysis of both native and hybrid mobile applications."/>
                        <outline text="Some of the key features of MobSF include dynamic analysis capabilities such as in-app SSL certificate pinning bypass, runtime manipulation, and API monitoring, as well as static analysis features such as reverse engineering, binary analysis, and decompilation."/>
                        <outline text="MobSF is widely used by mobile app developers, security researchers, and penetration testers to test and secure mobile applications. It is available as a command-line tool as well as a graphical user interface, making it easy to use and accessible to a wide range of users."/>
